FBIS4-29585 "dreas118_a_94015" FBIS-EAS-94-118 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Minister Comments on DPRK Issues in Beijing Minister Comments on DPRK Issues in Beijing Returns From DPRK Visit OW1806145894 Tokyo KYODO in English 1432 GMT 18 Jun 94 OW1806145894 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Narita, Chiba Pref., June 18 KYODO -- Former defense chief Taku Yamasaki returned home Saturday [18 June)( night via Beijing from a visit to North Korea. Yamasaki, a Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) member of the House of Representatives and former director general of the Defense Agency, had met senior officials of the (North) Korean Workers' Party to press for a diplomatic solution to the dispute over North Korea's suspected nuclear arms program. Also returning home was Yoichi Tani, another LDP lawmaker who accompanied Yamasaki on the visit to Pyongyang.
